also prefixed to the commentary of ServiuS, which, although it is for the most part merely a confused abridgment of the work of SuetoniuS, contains some additional matter, notably the statement that the lines about Helen in the second Aeneid (vv. 566 soll.) were Virgil's own, and were struck out of his manuscript by Varius and Tucca.

The memoir by Suetonius, in the form in which we now possess it, does not perhaps contain all that Suetonius wrote about Virgil, but so far as it extends its value is all-important.
